  "prompt": "Which are the best poems about India?",
  "response": "India has inspired countless poets both within the country and around the world. If you're looking for some of the best poems about India, here are a few that stand out:\n\n### By Indian Poets:\n1. **\"Where the Mind is Without Fear\" by Rabindranath Tagore**: A deeply patriotic poem, part of his acclaimed work Gitanjali. It envisions an ideal India.\n2. **\"A Love Song for India\" by Vikram Seth**: Reflects the poet\u2019s personal connection and love for the country.\n3. **\"The Slave\u2019s Dream\" by Henry Louis Vivian Derozio**: An early Indian poet who beautifully expressed the yearning for freedom and dignity.\n4. **\"An Ode to the Republic\" by Sarojini Naidu**: Naidu, also known as the Nightingale of India, wrote extensively about the country.\n5. **\"Tryst with Destiny\" by Jawaharlal Nehru**: Although prose, it is often considered poetic for its powerful imagery and emotion.\n\n### By International Poets:\n1. **\"On the Indian Sect Maharishi\" by Ralph Waldo Emerson**: A poem reflecting Emerson's fascination with Indian spirituality.\n2. **\"In India\" by Allan Ginsberg**: Captures the American poet\u2019s experiences in India with vivid imagery.\n\n### More Contemporary Works:\n1. **\"Mother India\" by Eunice de Souza**: A poem that provides a critical perspective on modern issues facing the country.\n2. **\"Partition\" by Kamala Das**: The pain and sorrow of the partition are beautifully articulated by this acclaimed poet.\n3. **\"My Sister\u2019s Bible\" by Meena Alexander**: Reflects on the complexities of identity and belonging, intertwined with Indian heritage.\n\nThese poems provide a rich tapestry of views on India, from its cultural heritage and spiritual depth to the political struggles and societal challenges. Each poet brings a unique perspective, making the list diverse and comprehensive.",
